<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6176> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6176" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Brutus and Cassius in late 43 or early in 42 to invite aid from the Parthians (Vell. 2.78.1; Flor. 2.19.4; Dio 48.24.5; cf. Liv. Per. 127; Ruf. Fest. Brev. 18.1), and after their defeat at Philippi remained and incited them to invade the eastern Roman provinces (see 40, Promagistrates, on Ventidius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10482> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10482" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Following the defeat of Brutus and Cassius at Philippi, Labienus remained in Parthia in the service of King Orodes" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10481> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10481" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "With Pacorus, co-commander of the Parthian invasion of the eastern provinces. Labienus enjoyed considerable success until defeated and executed by Ventidius Bassus in 39." .
